org.dice_research.squirrel.queue

Class AbstractGroupingQueue<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.dice_research.squirrel.queue.AbstractGroupingQueue<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BlockingQueue<T>, UriQueue
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractDomainBasedQueue, AbstractIpAddressBasedQueue

    public abstract class AbstractGroupingQueue<T>
extends Object
implements BlockingQueue<T>
    This abstract class manages two important aspects of a queue. It uses a mutex to access the queue and it manages a set containing Domains that are currently blocked by one of the workers.
    Author:
    Geraldo de Souza Junior (gsjunior@mail.uni-paderborn.de)
